-- German minister says all Opel bidders in running
-- 
-- Fri May 22, 2009 11:29am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/05/22/us-gm-opel-minister-sb-idUSTRE54L4AZ20090522

 

 BERLIN  (Reuters) - Germany's economy minister said on Friday that a host of questions remained about Canadian car parts group Magna's bid for Opel and that rival bidders remained in the running for the General Motors unit. 

 Karl-Theodor zu Guttenberg said a decision on the future of Opel needed to be taken next week. (Reporting by Matthias Sobolewski; Writing by  Noah Barkin )